  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "Indexed\n64\n18\n\nessential prophetic message. \"St. Sophia will be born again; she was not acceptable before,\" which beyond doubt refers to the second coming. + my experience of the two, mutually opposing worlds: the BIP + the PTG. What \"Tears\" shows most -in terms of God's presence- is the love expressed -+ felt- at the end scene at the all-night gas station; + this came to me in, by + through the dream - which in itself is an apocalyptic vision of the eschatological Judge (hence he condemns Jason",
      "matched_alias": "Asher",
      "term_id": "TERM_asher",
      "term_name": "Asher",
      "term_slug": "asher"
    },
    {
      "text": "Indexed\n58\n39\n\nof the template by which the Zoroastrian apocalyptic, Messianic reality can be seen clearly points to the role + nature of Valis being the revealer, or messenger. But it is not God that is disclosed: it is the meaning of history: the dialectic; for example, the Empire is revealed. The activity + events of this world are uncovered, not the divine nature. Not God but the way to God is revealed. The issues are revealed. Yet, Valis itself is revealed, which I took to be God. Now I vie",
      "matched_alias": "Messianic",
      "term_id": "TERM_messianic",
      "term_name": "Messianic",
      "term_slug": "messianic"
    }
  ],
